<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Good-man" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Good-man</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Goodman</orth> <emph>(Goódman)</emph> a familiar appellation, == a) gaffer: <cit><quote>I'll lay my head to any --'s hat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.310" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 310</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>g. baldpate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.328" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 328</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>g. Verges,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 5, 10</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 14</bibl>. <cit><quote>g. boy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 79</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 48</bibl>. b) husband: <cit><quote>my men should call me lord: I am your g.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 107.</bibl></cit>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>